   *True Seeing*

   *School* divination; *Level* cleric 5, druid 7, sorcerer/wizard 6

   *Casting Time* 1 standard action

   *Components* V, S, M (an eye ointment that costs 250 gp)

   *Range* touch

   *Target* creature touched

   *Duration* 1 min./level

   *Saving Throw*[Will] negates (harmless); **note Spell Resistance:
#spell-resistance.* yes (harmless)

   You confer on the subject the ability to see all things as they
actually are. The subject sees through normal and magical darkness,
notices secret doors hidden by magic, sees the exact locations of
creatures or objects under _[blur]_or _[displacement]_effects, sees
[invisible] creatures or objects normally, sees through illusions, and
sees the true form of polymorphed, changed, or transmuted things.
Further, the subject can focus its vision to see into the Ethereal
