4.1.1 Determine Bonuses
-----------------------

Each ability, after changes made because of race, has a modifier
ranging from -5 to +5. [Table: Ability Modifiers and Bonus Spells]
shows the modifier for each score. The modifier is the number you apply
to the die roll when your character tries to do something related to
that ability. You also use the modifier with some numbers that aren't
die rolls. A positive modifier is called a bonus, and a negative
modifier is called a penalty. The table also shows bonus spells, which
you'll need to know about if your character is a spellcaster.


